                  "code": "67781-5",
                  "display": "Summarization of encounter note"
                }
              ]
            },
            "title": "Synthesis"
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">Dear colleague, I am writing to inform you regarding the discharge of your 75-year-old male patient, admitted on 20/02/2021 due to substance dependence. Upon admission, a comprehensive psychiatric and medical assessment was conducted, confirming polysubstance dependence syndrome. Withdrawal monitoring was initiated immediately, with close observation for complications including delirium and seizure risk. The patient received structured detoxification support, pharmacological withdrawal management, and nutritional supplementation. Psychological counselling sessions were provided alongside motivational intervention. Social work assessment was completed to evaluate home circumstances and support needs. The patient remained medically stable throughout and was discharged on 28/02/2021 in a treated and stabilised condition. We recommend close follow-up in primary care, referral to community substance misuse services, and continued monitoring of physical and mental health. Medication details are enclosed. Please do not hesitate to contact us should you require further information.</div>"
            },
